S|# 21 · Idea Feed (Build · Software Factory)|> The intake for the software factory — proposed product/build ideas that can become projects in the Software pl. Sidebar badge: 94.
S|Purpose|A continuously growing feed of ideas for things to build (products, features, tools). It's the top of the Software Factory funnel: ideas accumulate here (badge shows **94**), the best get promoted into the **Software pl** as projects/PRs.
S|What it covers (inferred from context)|- A stream of **idea cards** — product concepts, feature ideas, internal tools — likely sourced from the owner, agents, Isaac's trends, and Advisory Council recommendations. // - Triage actions per card: promote to a project (into Software pl), defer, or reject — consistent with the ap/defer/reject pattern used across the app. // - Tagging by workspace and type; the large badge (94) implies a backlog that gets filtered down.
S|Relationship to other screens|- Feeds **Software pl** (`22`) where promoted ideas become coded projects (Nexus) under QA (Steve). // - Receives inputs from **Trend Radar** (`20`) and **Advisory Council** (`03`). // > **Confidence:** Listed in the sidebar (BUILD · SOFTWARE FACTORY) with a 94 badge, but not shown as a dedicated screen. Layout above is *inferred* from its name, badge, and position in the build funnel.